*cinnamon-2.6.13-r1 (11 Nov 2015)

  11 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> -cinnamon-2.6.13.ebuild,
  +cinnamon-2.6.13-r1.ebuild:
  RDEP virtual/python-imaging to dev-python/pillow

   virtual/python-imaging is obsolete.
  dev-python/pillow should be depended on.

  09 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-2.6.13.ebuild:
  settings-daemon: Add newly for add IUSE="pulseaudio"

   Change pulseaudio to optional in cinnamon-settings-daemon.

   And also,
  cinnamon[pulseaudio=] and cinnamon-control-center[pulseaudio=] are needed.

  09 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-2.6.13.ebuild:
  control-center: Add IUSE="pulseaudio"

   cinnamon-control-center[-pulseaudio] results to omit the sound panel.

   And gnome-extra/cinnamon depends on cinnamon-control-center[pulseaudio=].

  09 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-2.6.13.ebuild,
  +files/cinnamon-disable-pulseaudio.patch:
  Add IUSE="pulseaudio" for drop depending on PulseAudio

   It enables to install without PulseAudio (libpulse).
  Its side-effect is removing GVC (GNOME volume Control).

  09 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> cinnamon-2.6.13.ebuild:
  Depends on cinnamon-control-center[networkmanager=]

   When -networkmanager,
  cinnamon-control-center[-networkmanager] is also needed.
  Vice versa when +networkmanager.

*cinnamon-2.6.13 (03 Nov 2015)

  03 Nov 2015; wjn <wjn@aol.jp> +cinnamon-2.6.13.ebuild,
  +files/cinnamon-2.2.6-automagic-gnome-bluetooth.patch,
  +files/cinnamon-2.4.5-background.patch,
  +files/cinnamon-2.4.5-gnome-3.14.patch,
  +files/cinnamon-2.6.13-test-recorder-includes.patch,
  +files/cinnamon-2.6.7-optional-networkmanager.patch,
  +files/cinnamon-2.6.7-set-wheel.patch, +files/cinnamon-screensaver.desktop,
  +files/cinnamon2d-screensaver.desktop,
  +files/polkit-cinnamon-authentication-agent-1.desktop, +metadata.xml:
  Add for removing nm-applet from *.session when -networkmanager.

   nm-applet should be removed from RequiredComponents in cinnamon*.session,
  because nm-applet is not required when USE="-networkmanager".
  Maybe most users prefering USE="-networkmanager" don't install nm-applet.

